ciscoMvpnMIB.name: ciscoMvpnMIB
ciscoMvpnMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems, Inc. 170 Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS EMail: cs-ipmulticast@cisco.com
ciscoMvpnMIB.description: This MIB contains managed object definitions for Cisco implementation of multicast in VPNs defined by the Internet draft: draft-rosen-vpn-mcast-05.txt. Note that this MIB works along with the L3VPN-MPLS-VPN-MIB.

ciscoMvpnMvrfNumber.name: ciscoMvpnMvrfNumber
ciscoMvpnMvrfNumber.description: The number of MVRFs that are present in this device.

ciscoMvpnNotificationEnable.name: ciscoMvpnNotificationEnable
ciscoMvpnNotificationEnable.description: If this object is TRUE, then the generation of all notifications defined in this MIB is enabled.

ciscoMvpnGenericTable.name: ciscoMvpnGenericTable
ciscoMvpnGenericTable.description: This table gives the generic information about the MVRFs present in this device.

ciscoMvpnGenericEntry.name: ciscoMvpnGenericEntry
ciscoMvpnGenericEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every MVRF in the device. Note that many implementations may have MVRF for global VRF (VRF0) by default in the device. Also note that existence of the correspoding VRF in L3VPN-MPLS-VPN-MIB is necessary for a row to exist in this table. Deletion of corresponding VRF in L3VPN-MPLS-VPN-MIB also results in deletion of a row here. But deletion of a row ie deletion of a MVRF here does not result in the deletion of the corresponding VRF in L3VPN-MPLS-VPN-MIB.

ciscoMvpnGenOperStatusChange.name: ciscoMvpnGenOperStatusChange
ciscoMvpnGenOperStatusChange.description: This object describes the last operational change that happened for the given MVRF. createdMvrf - indicates that the MVRF was created in the device. deletedMvrf - indicates that the MVRF was deleted from the device. A row in this table will never have ciscoMvpnGenOperStatusChange equal to deletedMvrf(2), because in that case the row itself will be deleted from the table. This value for ciscoMvpnGenOperStatusChange is defined mainly for use in ciscoMvpnMvrfChange notification. modifiedMvrfDefMdtConfig - indicates that the default MDT group for the MVRF was configured, deleted or changed. modifiedMvrfDataMdtConfig - indicates that the data MDT group range or a associated variable (like the threshold) for the MVRF was configured, deleted or changed.

ciscoMvpnGenOperChangeTime.name: ciscoMvpnGenOperChangeTime
ciscoMvpnGenOperChangeTime.description: The time at which the last operational change for the MVRF in question took place. The last operational change is specified by ciscoMvpnGenOperStatusChange.

ciscoMvpnGenAssociatedInterfaces.name: ciscoMvpnGenAssociatedInterfaces
ciscoMvpnGenAssociatedInterfaces.description: Total number of interfaces associated with this MVRF (including the MDT tunnel interface) with ifOperStatus = up(1).

ciscoMvpnGenRowStatus.name: ciscoMvpnGenRowStatus
ciscoMvpnGenRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create or delete a row in this table.

ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultTable.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultTable
ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultTable.description: This table specifies the default MDT address and the encapsulation type used for a MVRF instance.

ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultEntry.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultEntry
ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every MVRF for which a default MDT group is configured. A MVRF which does not have a default MDT group configured will not appear in this table. Creation of a row in this table is the equivalent of configuring default MDT address for the given MVRF. Deletion of a row in this table is the equivalent of deconfiguring default MDT address for the given MVRF.

ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultAddrType
ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultAddress.

ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultAddress.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultAddress
ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultAddress.description: The default MDT address to be used for the MVRF in question.

ciscoMvpnMdtEncapsType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtEncapsType
ciscoMvpnMdtEncapsType.description: The encapsulation type to be used in the MVRF in question.

ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultRowStatus.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultRowStatus
ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify or delete a row in this table.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataTable.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataTable
ciscoMvpnMdtDataTable.description: This table specifies the range of data MDT addresses and associated variables for a MVRF instance.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataEntry.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataEntry
ciscoMvpnMdtDataEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every MVRF for which a data MDT group range is configured. A MVRF which does not have a data MDT group range configured will not appear in this table. Creation of a row in this table is the equivalent of configuring data MDT addresses for the given MVRF. Deletion of a row in this table is the equivalent of deconfiguring data MDT address usage in the given MVRF. Note that ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultEntry for a MVRF should be present in the device before ciscoMvpnMdtDataEntry for that MVRF can be created.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddrType
ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddress.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddress.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddress
ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddress.description: The data MDT group range address for the given MVRF. This along with ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardBits gives the pool of data MDT addresses that can be used for encapsulation in the MVRF upon data MDT switchover.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardType
ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardBits.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardBits.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardBits
ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardBits.description: Wildcard bits which when used along with data MDT range address, give a pool of addresses to be used in a MVRF. For example, if ciscoMvpnMdtDataRangeAddress is 239.1.2.0 and ciscoMvpnMdtDataWildcardBits is 0.0.0.3, the possible data MDT addresses are 239.1.2.0, 239.1.2.1, 239.1.2.2 and 239.1.2.3. Note that wild card bits should be right contiguous.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataThreshold.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataThreshold
ciscoMvpnMdtDataThreshold.description: The bandwidth threshold value which when exceeded for a multicast routing entry in the given MVRF, triggers usage of data MDT address instead of default MDT address for encapsulation.

ciscoMvpnMdtDataRowStatus.name: ciscoMvpnMdtDataRowStatus
ciscoMvpnMdtDataRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify or delete a row in this table.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtTable.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtTable
ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtTable.description: Given a multicast routing entry and the context MVRF, this table provides information about the MDT group being used for encapsulating the traffic for the multicast routing entry in the provider network at the instance of querying. Note that this table is a read-only table and is the result of the default MDT and data MDT configurations and the operational conditions like the traffic rate and sometimes, the implementation choices.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtEntry.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtEntry
ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtEntry.description: An entry in this table exists for a multicast routing entry the traffic for which is being encapsulated in a context MVRF.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGrpAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGrpAddrType
ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGrpAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGroup.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGroup
ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGroup.description: Group adddress of multicast routing entry in question.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSrcAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSrcAddrType
ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSrcAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSource.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSource.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSource
ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSource.description: Source adddress of the multicast routing entry in question.

ciscoMvpnMrouteUpDownStreamInfo.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteUpDownStreamInfo
ciscoMvpnMrouteUpDownStreamInfo.description: Indicates if this PE is the upstream (sending) or the downstream (receiving) router for the multicast routing entry specified by ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSource and ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGroup in the context MVRF specified by mplsVpnVrfName. Note that there may be two rows for the same multicast routing entry if the traffic is bi-directional, one row for PE as an upstream router the other for PE as the downstream router.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtGrpAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtGrpAddrType
ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtGrpAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtGroup.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtGroup
ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtGroup.description: MDT group address used to encapsulate the multicast routing entry specified by ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfSource and ciscoMvpnMrouteMvrfGroup in the context MVRF specified by mplsVpnVrfName.

ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtType.name: ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtType
ciscoMvpnMrouteMdtType.description: Indicates the type of MDT group used for encapsulation.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateTable.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateTable
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateTable.description: This table has information about the BGP advertisement of the the MDT groups. (These advertisements are generated and used for source discovery when SSM is used.)

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateEntry.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateEntry
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateEntry.description: An entry in this table is created when a BGP advertisement of the MDT group is received and cached in the PE device. An entry in this table deleted when such a cached BGP MDT update is withdrawn.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdGrpAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdGrpAddrType
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdGrpAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateGroup.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateGroup.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateGroup
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateGroup.description: MDT group address in the BGP MDT advertisement.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateRd.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateRd
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateRd.description: RD (route distinguisher) in the BGP MDT advertisement. This is the RD corresponding to the originator PE.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdSrcAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdSrcAddrType
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdSrcAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateSource.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateSource.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateSource
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateSource.description: MDT source address in the BGP MDT advertisement.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdOrigAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdOrigAddrType
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdOrigAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateOriginator.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateOriginator.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateOriginator
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateOriginator.description: The BGP peering address of the device that originated (or advertized) the BGP MDT update.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdNhAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdNhAddrType
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdNhAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateNexthop.

ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateNexthop.name: ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateNexthop
ciscoMvpnBgpMdtUpdateNexthop.description: The next-hop address (address of the border router to be used to reach the destination network) in the BGP MDT advertisement.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvTable.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvTable
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvTable.description: This table has information about the data MDT join TLVs received by a device.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvEntry.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvEntry
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvEntry.description: An entry in this table is created or updated for every MDT data join TLV received and cached in the device. The value of mplsVpnVrfName in such an entry specifies the name of the MVRF for which the data MDT groups from the TLVs are used.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvGrpAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvGrpAddrType
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvGrpAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvGroup.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvGroup
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvGroup.description: Data MDT group address in the MDT join TLV.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvSrcAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvSrcAddrType
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvSrcAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvSource.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvSource.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvSource
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvSource.description: Source address for the MDT multicast routing entry created following the receipt of MDT join TLV.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvUpTime.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvUpTime
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvUpTime.description: The time since this MDT join TLV was first received by the device.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvExpTime.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvExpTime
ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvExpTime.description: The amount of time remaining before the cache corresponding to this MDT join TLV is deleted from the device and the corresponding MDT multicast routing entry is marked as a non-MDT entry. Note that multiple TLVs for a data MDT group may be received by a device. Upon receipt, the expiry timer of an already existing entry is restarted and so ciscoMvpnMdtJnRcvExpTime is updated.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendTable.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendTable
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendTable.description: This table specifies the data MDT Join TLVs sent by a device.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendEntry.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendEntry
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendEntry.description: Entries in this table exist for data MDT Join TLVs that are being sent by this device to other PEs.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGrpAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGrpAddrType
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGrpAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGroup.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGroup
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGroup.description: This indicates the address of a multicast group in the MVRF specified by the column mplsVpnVrfName. This along with ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSource identifies the multicast routing entry for which the MDT join TLV is sent.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSrcAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSrcAddrType
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSrcAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSource.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSource.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSource
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendSource.description: This indicates the address of a source in the MVRF specified by the column mplsVpnVrfName. This, along with ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendGroup identifies the multicast routing entry for which the MDT join TLV is sent.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGrpAddrType.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGrpAddrType
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGrpAddrType.description: The Internet address type of ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGroup.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGroup
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGroup.description: The data MDT group in the MDT Join TLV sent.

ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtRefCt.name: ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtRefCt
ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtRefCt.description: Indicates how many multicast routing entries in the MVRF specified by the column mplsVpnVrfName are using ciscoMvpnMdtJnSendMdtGroup for encapsulation.

ciscoMvpnTunnelTable.name: ciscoMvpnTunnelTable
ciscoMvpnTunnelTable.description: This table gives information about the MVPN/MDT tunnels present in the device.

ciscoMvpnTunnelEntry.name: ciscoMvpnTunnelEntry
ciscoMvpnTunnelEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every MVPN tunnel interface present in the device. The ifType for a MVPN tunnel is 'tunnel' (131). (A MVPN tunnel interface should have relevant generic support in the IF-MIB and in the internet draft, draft-thaler-inet-tunnel-mib. Only MVPN specific aspects of such a tunnel interface are to be specified in this table.)

ciscoMvpnTunnelName.name: ciscoMvpnTunnelName
ciscoMvpnTunnelName.description: The canonical name assigned to the tunnel. The ifName of this tunnel interface should have a value equal to ciscoMvpnTunnelName.

ciscoMvpnTunnelMvrf.name: ciscoMvpnTunnelMvrf
ciscoMvpnTunnelMvrf.description: Name of the MVRF that this tunnel is associated with. This object has the same value as mplsVpnVrfName for the MVRF.

ciscoMvpnMvrfChange.name: ciscoMvpnMvrfChange
ciscoMvpnMvrfChange.description: A ciscoMvpnMvrfChange notification signifies a change about a MVRF in the device. The change event can be creation of the MVRF, deletion of the MVRF or an update on the default or data MDT configuration of the MVRF. The change event is indicated by ciscoMvpnGenOperStatusChange embedded in the notification. The user can then query ciscoMvpnGenericTable, ciscoMvpnMdtDefaultTable and/or ciscoMvpnMdtDataTable to get the details of the change as necessary. Note: Since the creation of a MVRF is often followed by configuration of default and data MDT groups for the MVRF, more than one (three at most) notifications for a MVRF may be generated serially, and it is really not necessary to generate all three of them. An agent may choose to generate a notification for the last event only, that is for data MDT configuration. Similarly, deletion of default or data MDT configuration on a MVRF happens before a MVRF is deleted, it is recommended that the agent send the notification for MVRF deletion event only.

ciscoMvpnModuleFullCompliance.name: ciscoMvpnModuleFullCompliance
ciscoMvpnModuleFullCompliance.description: Compliance statement for agents that support read-create so that both configuration and monitoring can be accomplished via this MIB module.

ciscoMvpnModuleReadOnlyCompliance.name: ciscoMvpnModuleReadOnlyCompliance
ciscoMvpnModuleReadOnlyCompliance.description: Compliance statement for agents that support the monitoring of MVRFs via this MIB module.

ciscoMvpnScalarGroup.name: ciscoMvpnScalarGroup
ciscoMvpnScalarGroup.description: Collection of scalar objects required for MVPN management.

ciscoMvpnMIBGenericGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMIBGenericGroup
ciscoMvpnMIBGenericGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for MVPN MVRF management.

ciscoMvpnMIBMdtDefaultGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMIBMdtDefaultGroup
ciscoMvpnMIBMdtDefaultGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for MVPN default MDT group management.

ciscoMvpnMIBMdtDataGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMIBMdtDataGroup
ciscoMvpnMIBMdtDataGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for MVPN data MDT group management.

ciscoMvpnMIBMrouteMdtGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMIBMrouteMdtGroup
ciscoMvpnMIBMrouteMdtGroup.description: Collection of objects that list sources in a MVRF and the corresponding MDT groups.

ciscoMvpnMIBBgpMdtUpdateGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMIBBgpMdtUpdateGroup
ciscoMvpnMIBBgpMdtUpdateGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for MVPN BGP MDT updates related information.

ciscoMvpnMIBMdtJnRcvGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMIBMdtJnRcvGroup
ciscoMvpnMIBMdtJnRcvGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for management of MVPN MDT data joins received by a device.

ciscoMvpnMIBMdtJnSendGroup.name: ciscoMvpnMIBMdtJnSendGroup
ciscoMvpnMIBMdtJnSendGroup.description: Collection of objects needed for management of MVPN MDT data joins received by a device.

ciscoMvpnTunnelGroup.name: ciscoMvpnTunnelGroup
ciscoMvpnTunnelGroup.description: Objects required for MDT tunnel interface management.
